<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-741-210  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 741 210.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telecommuting Review: the Gordon Report  August 1 1990 v7 n8p2(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Teleworking &quot;down under&quot;: an overview. (teleworking in Australia)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wood, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Australia is currently experimenting with teleworking and theprospects of successfully applying this new work system seem veryencouraging.andP;  Teleworking has not really taken off yet inAustralia as it has in the US and other industrialized nations,but this may be changing.andP;  Four factors will probably cause use ofteleworking to grow rapidly in Australia: the problems brought onby a highly urbanized population, demographic shifts in the theworkforce that will increase the number of working mothers, thegrowing need and expense of employer-supplied child care, andAustralian advances in telecommunications technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Social IssuesTrendsTelecommutingAustralia.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>